SIMPLE: polymerize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polymerize
<hw>Pol"y*mer*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>To cause polymerization of; to produce polymers from; to increase
the molecular weight of, without changing the atomic proportions; thus,
certain acids <xex>polymerize</xex> aldehyde.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polymerize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Polymerize
<hw>Pol"y*mer*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>To
change into another substance having the same atomic proportions, but a
higher molecular weight; to undergo polymerization; thus, aldehyde
<xex>polymerizes</xex> in forming paraldehyde.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polymerous</ent>⟦br⟧
